{{Short description|Indian actor (born 1984)}} {{Use Indian English|date=December 2013}} {{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}} {{Infobox person | name = Gurmeet Choudhary | image = Gurmeet Choudhary in 2017.jpg | caption = Choudhary in 2017 at [[Ravi Dubey]]'s birthday | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1984|2|22|df=yes}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/amp/photogallery/movies/happy-birthday-gurmeet-choudhary-a-look-at-his-most-romantic-pictures-with-wife-debina-bonnerjee-3460151.html|title=Happy Birthday Gurmeet Chaudhary: A look at his most romantic pictures with wife Debina Bonnerjee|work=[[News 18]]}}</ref> | birth_place = [[Bhagalpur]], [[Bihar]], [[India]] | occupation = Actor, dancer, martial artist, singer | years_active = 2006{{ndash}}present | notable_works = {{hlist|''[[Khamoshiyan (film)|Khamoshiyan]]''|''[[Wajah Tum Ho]]''|''[[Paltan (film)|Paltan]]''|''[[Geet – Hui Sabse Parayi]]''|''[[Ramayan (2008 TV series)|Ramayan]]''|''[[Punar Vivah]]''|}} | spouse = {{marriage|[[Debina Bonnerjee]]|2011}} | children = 2 }} '''Gurmeet Choudhary''' (born 22 February 1984) is an Indian actor and [[Martial arts|martial artist]]. He is known for his portrayal of Rama in ''[[Ramayan (2008 TV series)|Ramayan]]'', Maan Singh Khurana in ''[[Geet – Hui Sabse Parayi]]'' and Yash Suraj Pratap Sindhina in ''[[Punar Vivaah - Zindagi Milegi Dobara]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/ramayan-2008-gurmeet-choudhary-reveals-how-eating-olives-instead-of-berries-landed-him-in-the-hospital/articleshow/76393266.cms|title=Ramayan 2008: Gurmeet Choudhary reveals how eating olives instead of berries landed him in the hospital|access-date=16 June 2020|archive-date=16 June 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200616054014/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/ramayan-2008-gurmeet-choudhary-reveals-how-eating-olives-instead-of-berries-landed-him-in-the-hospital/articleshow/76393266.cms|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/how-gurmeet-choudhary-came-to-debina-bonnerjees-rescue-on-the-sets-of-ramayan/articleshow/75887965.cms|title=How Gurmeet Choudhary came to Debina Bonnerjee's rescue on the sets of 'Ramayan'|access-date=16 June 2020|archive-date=24 May 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200524044859/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/how-gurmeet-choudhary-came-to-debina-bonnerjees-rescue-on-the-sets-of-ramayan/articleshow/75887965.cms|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2012, Gurmeet participated in ''[[Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa 5]]'' and emerged as the winner. He also participated in ''[[Nach Baliye 6]]'' and ''[[Fear Factor: Khatron Ke Khiladi 5]]'' and emerged as the 1st runner-up in both. He made his film debut with [[20th Century Fox|Fox Studio's]] psychological thriller and horror ''[[Khamoshiyan (film)|Khamoshiyan]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/tv/news-interviews/I-want-to-be-a-Bollywood-star-Gurmeet-Choudhary/articleshow/29665822.cms |title=I want to be a Bollywood star: Gurmeet Choudhary – The Times of India |publisher=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com |date=2014-02-01 |access-date=2014-05-28 |archive-date=11 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180911083627/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/tv/news-interviews/I-want-to-be-a-Bollywood-star-Gurmeet-Choudhary/articleshow/29665822.cms |url-status=live }}</ref>
==Early life and background== Gurmeet was born in Jairampur village in Bhagalpur, Bihar, India.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abplive.com/states/bihar/gurmeet-choudhary-in-his-village-jairampur-bhagalpur-with-wife-debina-shares-photo-with-emotional-note-1985848|title=Gurmeet Choudhary in Patna: अपने गांव जयरामपुर पहुंचे टीवी के ‘राम’ गुरमीत चौधरी, पत्नी के साथ शेयर की तस्वीर}}</ref> The Gurmeet Choudhary Foundation launched a post-Covid specialised care centre at his hometown.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/gurmeet-choudharys-foundation-opens-the-first-ever-post-covid-specialised-care-centre-at-his-hometown-bihar/articleshow/83670681.cms|title=Gurmeet Choudhary's foundation opens the first ever post COVID centre}}</ref> His elder brother is a general physician in his hometown.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/i-am-proud-of-my-doctor-brother-working-in-bihar-but-worried-too-gurmeet/story-6oM6cxUsKDqzhkZDDPcocN.html|title=I am proud of my doctor brother working in Bihar but worried too: Gurmeet}}</ref>
== Personal life ==
On 15 February 2011, Choudhary married actress [[Debina Bonnerjee]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |title=Gurmeet Choudhary-Debina Bonnerjee Marry Again But This Time In Bengali Tradition {{!}} View Pics |url=https://www.india.com/entertainment/tv-news-gurmeet-choudhary-debina-bonnerjee-marry-again-this-time-bengali-tradition-view-pics-5021897/ |access-date=2022-04-05 |website=www.india.com |language=en}}</ref> On 4 October 2021, they married again.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Debina Bonnerjee And Gurmeet Choudhary "Finally" Have A Bengali Wedding, 10 Years After They Got Married |url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/debina-bonnerjee-and-gurmeet-choudhary-finally-have-a-bengali-wedding-10-years-after-they-got-married-2563438 |access-date=2022-04-05 |website=NDTV.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |last2= |first2= |last3= |first3= |title=Gurmeet Choudhary-Debina Bonnerjee renew their vows in Bengali wedding in Kolkata |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/television/celebrity/story/gurmeet-choudhary-debina-bonnerjee-renew-their-vows-in-bengali-wedding-in-kolkata-1861053-2021-10-05 |access-date=2022-04-05 |website=India Today |language=en}}</ref> On 3 April 2022, they had their first child, a girl.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-04-05 |title=Debina Bonnerjee-Gurmeet Choudhary welcome baby girl, share her first video: ‘With utmost gratitude…’ |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/television/debina-bonnerjee-gurmeet-choudhary-welcome-baby-girl-share-first-video-with-utmost-gratitude-7851952/ |access-date=2022-04-05 |website=The Indian Express |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-04-04 |title=Debina Bonnerjee and Gurmeet Choudhary become parents to baby girl, share first glimpse of child. |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/tv/debina-bonnerjee-and-gurmeet-choudhary-become-parents-to-baby-girl-share-first-glimpse-of-child-watch-video-101649051887736.html |access-date=2022-04-05 |website=Hindustan Times |language=en}}</ref>
== Career == Gurmeets first gained prominence through his portrayal of [[Rama]] in the 2009 television series [[Ramayan (2008 TV series)|Ramayan]], opposite [[Debina Bonnerjee]] who played the role of [[Sita]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/exclusive-gurmeet-and-i-would-actually-fight-about-who-would-get-into-the-makeup-seat-first-so-the-other-could-catch-up-on-some-sleep-debina-bonnerjee/articleshow/76306731.cms|title=Exclusive - Gurmeet and I would actually fight about who would get into the makeup seat first, so the other could catch up on some sleep: Debina Bonnerjee|access-date=16 June 2020|archive-date=12 June 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200612002743/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/exclusive-gurmeet-and-i-would-actually-fight-about-who-would-get-into-the-makeup-seat-first-so-the-other-could-catch-up-on-some-sleep-debina-bonnerjee/articleshow/76306731.cms|url-status=live}}</ref> Choudhary participated in the reality show ''[[Pati Patni Aur Woh (TV series)|Pati Patni Aur Woh]]'' with his then fiancée, [[Debina Bonnerjee]] who also played Sita in ''Ramayan''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/gurmeet-choudhary-chants-om-mantra-to-drive-away-lockdown-anxiety/articleshow/76192110.cms|title=Gurmeet Choudhary chants 'Om' mantra to drive away lockdown anxiety|access-date=16 June 2020|archive-date=4 June 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200604191312/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/gurmeet-choudhary-chants-om-mantra-to-drive-away-lockdown-anxiety/articleshow/76192110.cms|url-status=live}}</ref> After this show, he played the role of a business magnate Maan Singh Khurana in ''[[Geet (TV series)|Geet – Hui Sabse Parayi]] alongside [[Drashti Dhami]]''. He played a lead role in the show ''[[Punar Vivah]] as Yash Sindhia, alongside [[Kratika Sengar]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/brunch/the-six-pack-ram-gurmeet-choudhary/story-klXw565hmCQhzETHVKM7HP.html|title=The Six Pack Ram Gurmeet Choudhary|date=18 October 2014|access-date=22 May 2017|archive-date=3 June 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170603063845/http://www.hindustantimes.com/brunch/the-six-pack-ram-gurmeet-choudhary/story-klXw565hmCQhzETHVKM7HP.html|url-status=live}}</ref>
Gurmeet participated in and won the fifth season of the popular dance contest ''[[Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa]]'' with choreographer Shampa Sonthalia. He competed in the dance contest ''[[Nach Baliye 6]]'' alongside his wife [[Debina Bonnerjee]], his co-star from ''Ramayan'', whom he had married in 2011, in which he finished as the first runner up.<ref>{{cite news|author=Richa Barua, TNN|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-02-17/tv/28554179_1_debina-bonnerjee-reality-show-honeymoon|title=All work, no honeymoon: Gurmeet, Debina|date=2011-02-17|access-date=2013-09-15|archive-date=3 January 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140103071942/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-02-17/tv/28554179_1_debina-bonnerjee-reality-show-honeymoon|work=[[The Times of India]]|url-status=dead}}</ref> They were choreographed by Pratik Utekar. He participated in an action reality show ''[[Fear Factor: Khatron Ke Khiladi (season 5)]]'' where he was named the first runner-up.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://colors.in.com/in/khatronkekhiladi/contestant/gurmeet-choudhary-572.html |title=Gurmeet Choudhary Khatron ke khiladi Season 5 Contestants, Participants |publisher=Colors.in.com |access-date=2014-05-28 |archive-date=21 July 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150721172610/http://colors.in.com/in/khatronkekhiladi/contestant/gurmeet-choudhary-572.html |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/screen/gurmeet-debina-join-khatron-ke-khiladi-gang/ |title=Gurmeet- Debina join Khatron Ke Khiladi gang |publisher=The Indian Express |date=2014-02-12 |access-date=2014-05-28 |archive-date=20 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180920083937/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/screen/gurmeet-debina-join-khatron-ke-khiladi-gang/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/tv/Rajniesh-Duggall-wins-Fear-Factor-Khatron-Ke-Khiladi-season-5/photostory/35610828.cms |title=Gurmeet becomes Runner up in Fear Factor- Khatron Ke Khiladi season 5 |date=25 May 2014 |access-date=22 October 2014 |archive-date=19 November 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141119135314/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/tv/Rajniesh-Duggall-wins-Fear-Factor-Khatron-Ke-Khiladi-season-5/photostory/35610828.cms |url-status=live }}</ref>
Gurmeet Choudhary's first foray into the Bollywood film industry<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/gurmeet-choudhary-on-bagging-his-first-bollywood-film-it-was-mukesh-bhatts-wife-who-first-spotted-me-on-tv-playing-ram-in-ramayan/articleshow/75760475.cms|title=Gurmeet Choudhary on bagging his first Bollywood film: It was Mukesh Bhatt's wife, who first spotted me on TV playing Ram in Ramayan|access-date=16 June 2020|archive-date=17 May 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200517231958/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/gurmeet-choudhary-on-bagging-his-first-bollywood-film-it-was-mukesh-bhatts-wife-who-first-spotted-me-on-tv-playing-ram-in-ramayan/articleshow/75760475.cms|url-status=live}}</ref> was in 2015 when he was cast as the character of Jaidev in the psychological thriller Khamoshiyan, produced by Fox Studios India and [[Vishesh Films]].
He is also a trained martial artist.<ref>{{cite news|author=Mumbai Mirror|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-02-28/fitness/34749095_1_gurmeet-choudhary-martial-arts-punar-vivaah|title=8 years since samosas: Gurmeet Choudhary|date=2013-02-28|access-date=2013-09-15|archive-date=3 December 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203052357/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-02-28/fitness/34749095_1_gurmeet-choudhary-martial-arts-punar-vivaah|work=[[The Times of India]]|url-status=dead}}</ref>
