{{short description|American actress and musician}} {{Use mdy dates|date=April 2014}} {{BLP sources|date=June 2016}} {{Infobox person | name = Cassidy Freeman | image = Cassidy Freeman Oct 2014 (cropped).jpg | imagesize = 220px | caption = Freeman at the Stars Strike Out Child Abuse Celebrity Bowling Fundraiser on October 19, 2014 | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1982|04|22|mf=yes}} | birth_place = [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], U.S. | other_names = | occupation = Actress, singer, pianist | years_active = 2006–present | spouse(s) = {{marriage|Justin Carpenter|2012|2015|end=div.}} | partner = Ben Ellsworth | children = 1 | relatives = [[Crispin Freeman]] (brother) | website = | alma_mater = [[Middlebury College]] }}
'''Cassidy Freeman''' (born April 22, 1982)<ref name="TVG-bio">{{cite web |url=http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/cassidy-freeman/296936/ |title=Cassidy Freeman |work=[[TV Guide]] |access-date=2016-06-08}}</ref> is an American actress and musician. She is known for her roles as [[Tess Mercer]] in [[The CW]]'s superhero drama ''[[Smallville]]'', Amber Gemstone in the [[HBO]] series ''[[The Righteous Gemstones]]'', and Cady Longmire in [[A&E (TV network)|A&E]]'s modern western ''[[Longmire (TV series)|Longmire]]''.<ref name="AETV">{{cite web|url=http://www.aetv.com/longmire/cast/cassidy-freeman|title=Cassidy Freeman as Cady Longmire - Longmire Cast & Characters|publisher=A&E TV}}</ref>
==Early life and education== Freeman was born in [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]],<ref name="TVG-bio" /> to prominent Chicago-area attorneys Glynna and Lee Freeman, who also own a cattle ranch in [[Montana]]. She is the youngest of four children, with three brothers, two of whom are voice actor [[Crispin Freeman]] and musician Clark Freeman. Her third brother Ryan is adopted.<ref name=":0" /> Her father is [[Jewish]].<ref>{{cite tweet |last=Freeman |first=Crispin |author-link=Crispin Freeman |user=CrispinFreeman |number=15578078550 |date=June 6, 2010 |title=@binkxy Absolutely! My Jewish father would love that! |language=en |access-date=January 19, 2022}}</ref> Her mother has [[Germans|German]], [[English people|English]], [[Scottish people|Scottish]], and [[Irish people|Irish]] ancestry.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=Pillow Talking's Interview with Actress, Singer, Musician, Producer CASSIDY FREEMAN|url=http://somedayprods.com/talking/pillow-talkings-interview-with-actress-singer-musician-producer-cassidy-freeman/|access-date=2020-11-03|website=Pillow Talking|language=en-US}}</ref>
Freeman graduated from [[The Latin School of Chicago]], and then ''[[magna cum laude]]'' from [[Middlebury College]] in 2005 with [[Academic degree|degrees]] in theater and Spanish.{{citation needed|date=June 2020}}
==Career== [[File:CassidyFreemanComicCon - vagueonthehow 4.jpg|thumb|right|Freeman in 2010]]
===Acting=== Freeman has appeared in several [[Short film|shorts]], [[feature film]]s and television series. She starred in the thriller film ''YellowBrickRoad'' which was written and directed by Andy Mitton and Jesse Holland.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/34348/dont-follow-yellowbrickroad|title=DON'T Follow the YellowBrickRoad|work=[[Dread Central]]|date=June 5, 2012}}</ref> Freeman also played the character Veronica Sharpe in the award-winning short film ''Razor Sharp''. The film won "Best Action Film" at the 2007 Comic-Con International Independent Film Festival. In September 2008, she began starring in [[The CW]]'s [[Superman]]-inspired drama ''[[Smallville]]'' where she played [[Tess Mercer]] after the departure of [[Michael Rosenbaum]]'s [[Lex Luthor (Smallville)|Lex Luthor]] and continued in this role until the show ended in May 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bloody-disgusting.com/news/18354|title=Slamdance '10: First Stills from 'YellowBrickRoad'|work=[[Bloody Disgusting]]|date=December 11, 2009}}</ref>
Freeman has appeared three times in the [[CBS]] crime drama franchise [[CSI (franchise)|CSI]]. In October 2009, she appeared in ''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation]]'' season 10, episode four, called "[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation (season 10)|Coup de Grâce]]". In September 2011, she appeared in ''[[CSI: NY]]'' season 8, episode one, called "[[CSI: NY (season 8)|Indelible]]". In March 2012, she appeared in ''[[CSI: Miami]]'' season 10, episode fifteen, called "[[CSI: Miami (season 10)|No Good Deed]]".
On January 13, 2012, Freeman was confirmed to be in The CW's fantasy drama ''[[The Vampire Diaries]]'' as Sage in the third season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/49895/cassidy-freeman-goes-playboy-club-vampire-diaries|title=See the Extended Preview of The Vampire Diaries Episode 5.08 - Dead Man on Campus|date=November 15, 2013|work=[[Dread Central]]}}</ref> Between 2012 and 2017, Freeman starred as Cady Longmire in the [[A&E (TV channel)|A&E]] and (later) [[Netflix]] crime drama ''[[Longmire (TV series)|Longmire]]''.<ref name="AETV" /><ref name="collider"/>
Between 2016 and 2017, she played the Russian spy Eva Azarova in ''[[NCIS: New Orleans]]''. She also starred in a crossover episode with its parent series ''[[NCIS (TV series)|NCIS]]''. She co-starred alongside [[Will Patton]] in the fifth ''[[The Purge]]'' movie ''[[The Forever Purge]]'', which was released in 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Will Patton and Cassidy Freeman Join Blumhouse's New 'Purge' Thriller (Exclusive) {{!}} Hollywood Reporter|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/will-patton-cassidy-freeman-join-blumhouses-new-purge-thriller-1257483|access-date=2020-11-03|website=www.hollywoodreporter.com|date=November 22, 2019}}</ref>
===Music=== Freeman, her brother Clark Freeman, and Andy Mitton formed a band called The Real D'Coy, in which Freeman sings and plays the piano.<ref name="collider">{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/cassidy-freeman-longmire-interview/|title=Cassidy Freeman Talks LONGMIRE, SMALLVILLE, and Her Band, THE REAL D'COY|date=June 24, 2012|website=Collider.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Steven Eramo |url=http://www.newsarama.com/2804-lex-schmex-meet-smallville-s-tess-mercer.html |title='Lex Schmex' – Meet SMALLVILLE's Tess Mercer |website=Newsarama.com |date=May 1, 2009 |access-date=2016-06-08}}</ref>
===Allegations against Jeremy Piven=== In November 2017, Freeman accused actor [[Jeremy Piven]] of predatory behavior. Freeman accused Piven of trying to do something to her when she was young. She came forward with her allegations after actress Ariane Bellamar accused Piven of sexual harassment.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Delbyck|first=Cole|date=2017-11-02|title='Smallville' Actress Calls Out Jeremy Piven's 'Predatory Behavior'|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/smallville-actress-cassidy-freeman-slams-jeremy-piven-for-predatory-behavior_n_59fb1c73e4b01b474048a2ac|access-date=2020-11-03|website=HuffPost|language=en}}</ref>
==Personal life== In January 2022 Freeman announced that she was expecting her first child with her boyfriend Ben Ellsworth.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.silverscreenbeat.com/cassidy-freeman-star-of-longmire-announces-her-pregnancy/|title=Cassidy Freeman, star of 'Longmire,' announces her pregnancy|last=Wells|first=David|date=2022-01-27|access-date=2022-02-17|website=SilverScreenBeat|language=en}}</ref> Their daughter, Gigi Kaya Ellsworth was born on 6 February 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/CaOcxb_MNo7/|title=Cassidy Freeman's Instagram photo: "Welcome to the world, Gigi Kaya Ellsworth ✨✨on Feb 6th 2022 you came to join us and I am in awe of you, so wildly in love with you and very excited to get to know you.❤️❤️❤️"The longest baby I've ever seen" -our midwife"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2022-02-21}}</ref>
==Philanthropy== Freeman is an active member of the [[Heal the Bay]] charity, which works toward cleaning up and protecting the West Coast waters. She also tutors children in Santa Monica as part of the Virginia Avenue Project.<ref name=r1>{{cite web |url=http://cwtv.com/shows/smallville/cast/cassidy-freeman |title=Bios – Cassidy Freeman |publisher=CW TV |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101215120430/http://cwtv.com/shows/smallville/cast/cassidy-freeman |archive-date=2010-12-15}}</ref>
