{{short description|Swedish actor}} {{for|the Swedish sailor|John Harrysson}} {{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}} {{More citations needed|date=August 2012}} {{Infobox person | name = John Harryson | image = John Harrysson.jpg | imagesize = | alt = | caption = Harryson in 1986. | birthname = John Edvard Harryson | birth_date = {{Birth date|1926|4|17|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Katrineholm]], Sweden | death_date = {{Death date and age|2008|11|28|1926|4|17|df=yes}} | death_place = [[Stockholm]], Sweden | othername = | nationality = Swedish | occupation = Actor, voice actor, singer | yearsactive = 1946–2002 | spouse = {{married|Kajsa Hultare|1955|2003|end=her death}}<ref name="Uddling & Paabo (1992), p. 446">{{cite book |editor1-last=Uddling |editor1-first=Hans |editor2-last=Paabo |editor2-first=Katrin |date=1992 |title=Vem är det: svensk biografisk handbok. 1993 |trans-title=Who is it: Swedish biographical handbook. 1993 |location=Stockholm |publisher=Norstedt |isbn=91-1-914072-X |language=Swedish |url=http://runeberg.org/vemardet/1993/0446.html |page=446}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dn.se/arkiv/familj/kajsa-harryson-lysande-journalist-vallustig-sprakkonstnar/ |newspaper=[[Dagens Nyheter]] |title=Kajsa Harryson. Lysande journalist, vällustig språkkonstnär |trans-title=Kajsa Harryson. Brilliant journalist, voluptuous language artist |first=Finn |last=Afzelius |first2=Lena |last2=Rydin |first3=Harry |last3=Strand |date=2003-12-19 |access-date=3 January 2016 |language=Swedish}}</ref> | children = 4,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/nyheter/article11583762.ab |newspaper=[[Aftonbladet]] |title=John Harryson har avlidit |trans-title=John Harryson has died |first=Simon |last=Andréen |date=4 December 2008 |access-date=3 January 2016 |language=Swedish}}</ref> including [[Peter Harryson]] (with Dahl) | partner = Ulla-Britt Dahl | website = }}
'''John Edvard Harryson''' (17 April 1926 &ndash; 28 November 2008) was a [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[actor]]. He was the father of famous Swedish actor and television host [[Peter Harryson]].
Born in [[Katrineholm]], Harrysson was a renowned actor in Sweden. For a younger generation John Harrysson was known as the Swedish voice of [[Scrooge McDuck]], [[Eeyore]] in [[Winnie the Pooh]], [[Doctor Snuggles]], [[Bert (Sesame Street)|Bert]] in Svenska Sesam (The second Swedish version of [[Sesame Street]]), and the [[Sheriff of Nottingham]] in ''[[Robin Hood (1973 film)|Robin Hood]]'' (1973).
==Selected filmography== * ''[[Desire (1946 Swedish film)|Desire]]'' (1946) * ''[[Summer with Monika]]'' (1953) * ''[[Voyage in the Night]]'' (1955) * ''[[Darling of Mine]]'' (1955) * ''[[Andersson's Kalle (1972 film)|Andersson's Kalle]]'' (1972) * ''[[Woman Doctors]]'' (1984)
