{{short description|American video game composer}} {{Infobox musical artist | name = Jared Emerson-Johnson | image = JaredEmerson-Johnson_Conducting.jpeg | caption = Emerson-Johnson conducting a recording session at AudioSFX | birth_name = Jared Nathaniel Emerson-Johnson | birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1981|10|13}} | origin = [[San Francisco, California|San Francisco]], [[California]] | instrument = Vocals, keyboards, guitar, violin, mandolin, ukulele, banjo | genre = [[Jazz]], [[classical music|classical]] | occupation = Composer, voice actor, sound designer, voice director | years_active = 2002–present | website = [http://www.basound.com Bay Area Sound] }}
'''Jared Nathaniel Emerson-Johnson''' (born October 13, 1981) is an American [[video game music]] [[composer]], [[sound designer]], voice director and [[voice actor]]. Emerson-Johnson is the Music Supervisor and lead composer at Bay Area Sound, an audio production company specializing in sound design, music and voiceover for video games.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.jaredemersonjohnson.com |title=jaredemersonjohnson.com |accessdate=2020-11-27}}</ref>
==Career==
Jared began his career as an assistant to composer [[Clint Bajakian]] on the score for LucasArts' ''[[Indiana Jones and the Emperor's Tomb]]''. Emerson-Johnson has also worked as a sound designer for projects, including ''[[James Bond 007: Everything or Nothing]]'', ''[[The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King (video game)|The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King]]'', ''[[Psychonauts]]'', and ''[[Firewatch]]''. Emerson-Johnson is perhaps best known as the composer behind multiple video games produced by [[Telltale Games]], such as ''[[Bone: Out from Boneville|Bone]]'', ''[[Sam & Max]]'', ''[[Strong Bad's Cool Game for Attractive People]]'', ''[[Wallace & Gromit's Grand Adventures]]'', ''[[Poker Night at the Inventory]]'', ''[[Back to the Future: The Game]]'', ''[[Jurassic Park: The Game]]'', ''[[The Walking Dead (2012 video game)|The Walking Dead]]'', ''[[The Wolf Among Us]],'' ''[[Game of Thrones (2014 video game)|Game of Thrones]]'', ''[[Batman: The Telltale Series]]'', and ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy: The Telltale Series]]''.
In all three seasons of ''[[Sam & Max]]'', he voices the C.O.P.S., a group of obsolete computers. In ''[[Tales of Monkey Island]]'', he plays the Marquis DeSinge as well as the Thief.
In 2004, Emerson-Johnson received the [[Game Developers Conference|Game Audio Network Guild's]] "Rookie of the Year" award. Jared's score, voice direction, and sound design for Telltale Games' ''[[Bone: The Great Cow Race]]'' were finalists for the 2007 Independent Games Festival. His score for Telltale Games' ''[[Sam & Max Beyond Time and Space]]'' was also a finalist for Best Original Score in the 2008 IGN PC Awards. He shares an AdventureGamers.com 2009 Aggie award for best voice acting for his work on ''[[Tales of Monkey Island]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.adventuregamers.com/article/id,1128/p,11|title=2009 Aggie Awards|date=17 February 2010}}</ref>
His score for Telltale Games’ ''[[The Walking Dead (2012 video game)|The Walking Dead]]'' was nominated for Best Music of the year at the ''[[British Academy Games Awards]]'' in 2013.
