{{short description|French songwriter and singer (born 1979)}} {{Orphan|date=December 2021}}
{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2020}} {{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians --> | name = Lionel Neykov | image = | caption = | image_size = | background = solo_singer | birth_name = | alias = | birth_date = 1979 | death_date = | origin = Paris, France | instrument = vocals, guitar | genre = Singer-songwriter, [[Independent music|Indie]] | occupation = Singer, songwriter | years_active = | label = Self Publishing on [[CD Baby]] and [[iTunes]] | associated_acts = | website = [http://www.myspace.com/lionelneykov myspace.com/LionelNeykov] | current_members = | past_members = }}
'''Lionel Neykov''' is a French songwriter and singer.
He became very popular in Spain during Christmas 2008 after his song ''Freeze my senses'' was selected for the annual advertising campaign of the [[Spanish Christmas Lottery]].
==Biography== Born to a French mother and a Bulgarian father in Paris, he started playing the guitar when he was 21 years old. He soon started to write and record his own songs. At the age of 24, he moved to New York, where he currently lives.<ref>[http://latino.myspace.com/lionelneykovstreetteam Lionel Neykov Street Team Fan Page] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714144212/http://latino.myspace.com/lionelneykovstreetteam |date=July 14, 2011 }}</ref> In summer 2007 he started working on his first album; ''Songs of Want and Loss''.<ref>[http://www.myspace.com/lionelneykov Lionel Neykov page on MySpace]</ref>{{Primary source inline|date=January 2020}} After releasing his songs on YouTube and [[MySpace]], his song ''Freeze my senses'' was selected by the [[Advertising agency]] "[[Ricardo Pérez Asociados]]" for the television advertisement they were preparing for the [[Spanish Christmas Lottery]] campaign for 2008. When "Ricardo Pérez Asociados" was selected by the Spanish Lottery to produce the commercials, he was contacted again and got a US$20,000 deal<ref>[http://www.adn.es/ciudadanos/loterianavidad/20081203/NWS-0609-lionel-neykov-cancion-loteria-navidad.html ADN newspaper, December 3rd 2008] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081206050358/http://www.adn.es/ciudadanos/loterianavidad/20081203/NWS-0609-lionel-neykov-cancion-loteria-navidad.html |date=December 6, 2008 }}</ref> for the use of his song on the advertisement, twice what he was offered initially.
